{"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"centerOffset","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","remoteSource":{"fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159"},"roleHeading":"Instance Property","symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"text":"CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the left."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to zero and its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"text":" to half the height of the view.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","title":"centerOffset","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"title":"MLNAnnotation","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","type":"topic","title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"collection"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"title":"MLNAnnotationView","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen."}]}}}